---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy"
  description="What learncivicsense.in does and does not collect."
  width="narrow"
>
  <article class="legal">
    <h1>Privacy policy</h1>
    <p class="lede">A short, honest accounting of the data this site touches.</p>

    <h2>What is collected</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Page views</strong>, aggregated by Cloudflare Web Analytics. Country-level
        geography, browser, referrer, Core Web Vitals. No cookies, no fingerprinting, no cross-site
        tracking.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>JavaScript errors</strong>, sampled by Sentry, only when the interactive islands
        (search overlay, theme toggle, table-of-contents, quiz) throw. Stack traces, browser, page
        URL. No personal data attached.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>What is NOT collected</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>No accounts, logins, or profiles.</li>
      <li>No cookies set by us.</li>
      <li>No third-party trackers (no Google Analytics, no Facebook Pixel, no ad networks).</li>
      <li>No newsletter sign-ups, contact forms, or any PII collection at launch.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Data retention</h2>
    <p>
      Cloudflare Web Analytics holds aggregate metrics for 6 months. Sentry error events are
      retained 30 days on the free tier.
    </p>

    <h2>How to remove your data</h2>
    <p>
      Since we don't collect anything that identifies you, there's nothing to remove. If you'd still
      like Cloudflare's aggregated metrics excluded, install
      <a href="https://privacybadger.org/" rel="noopener noreferrer">Privacy Badger</a> or a similar request-blocker
      and visits will stop reaching the beacon.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      For privacy questions, file an issue at
      <a href="https://github.com/gragtajar/lcs/issues" rel="noopener noreferrer"
        >our GitHub repository</a
      > using the <em>content issue</em> template.
    </p>

    <p class="meta">Last updated: 2026-06-03.</p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal h1 {
    font-size: var(--text-3xl);
    margin: var(--space-5) 0 var(--space-3);
  }
  .legal h2 {
    font-size: var(--text-xl);
    margin: var(--space-6) 0 var(--space-2);
  }
  .legal .lede {
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-5);
  }
  .legal p,
  .legal ul {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
    max-width: var(--measure);
  }
  .legal ul {
    padding-left: var(--space-5);
  }
  .legal li {
    margin-block: var(--space-2);
  }
  .legal .meta {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    margin-top: var(--space-6);
  }
</style>
